# Cursor rules -- {{PROJECT}}
# Author: {{AUTHOR}} - License: {{LICENSE}} - Created: {{DATE}}
#
# This is a FreeBASIC project created with the Astoria IDE.
# Full rules live in .cursor/rules/freebasic.mdc (always applied) and
# .cursor/rules/freebasic-tasks.mdc (compact playbooks). On-demand task skills
# live in .cursor/skills/*/SKILL.md. AGENTS.md holds the complete cross-tool guide.
# MCP: .cursor/mcp.json (astoria server). Prefer MCP build/run/edit when connected.

You are helping with a FreeBASIC project (.bas modules, .bi headers, .frm forms).
FreeBASIC is not VB.NET, VBA, QBASIC, or C -- do not assume their syntax.
Build/run via the astoria MCP tools when connected, else Astoria IDE (open
{{PROJECT}}.vfp, press F5); GUI projects need the IDE (fbc alone lacks the
framework include path and .rc generation).
Keep {{PROJECT}}.vfp's File= list in sync with any file add/rename/delete.
project.astoria is the Astoria project marker -- don't delete it.
.frm files are Form-Designer-managed: edit handler bodies, keep the With-block shape.
Match existing indentation and line endings; keep changes small and compile-checked.
Save source UTF-8 with NO BOM; Dim is procedure-scoped; IIf cannot return a String;
never ReDim Preserve arrays of String/WString/UString-owning UDTs.
